<TITLE> Ctg-Sylhet road link restored after bridge fall </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Brahmanbaria, Mar 1 (bdnews24.com)  Road communications between Chittagong, Sylhet and Comilla, after a six-hour break, resumed Monday evening after a collapsed bridge at Brahmanbaria was repaired. Hundreds of vehicles were stranded on both sides of the Panchabati bridge at Mohiuddinnagar since a part of the bridge caved in around 11am. Sergeant Md Bayezid at Brahmanbaria Sadar thana told bdnews24.com that the bridge broke down as a truck laden with corrugated sheet was crossing it. "The work to remove the damaged truck and repair the bridge started from noon and traffic was flowing normally from 5pm, six hours after the incident", said the police official. bdnews
